   <note>The exterior and one page from Eliza Rhea Anderson Fain`s personal diary. This entry from the journal was written when Fain and all of her children suffered from the measles in May of 1843. The rest of the journal consists mainly of the Rhea family geneaology from the late 18th century until around 1840. The journal entries date from approximately the 1830s until the 1860s.</note>
